      <p>
        Smaller sizes in the 2.0 to 2.5 mm range usually fit better because stems are still fine and tender.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="scenarioCard">
      <h3>Best for Typical Home Vegetable Grafts</h3>
      <p>
        Mid-range sizes are often the most useful because many home-grown seedlings land there if timing is reasonably close.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="scenarioCard">
      <h3>Best for Slightly Overgrown Seedlings</h3>
      <p>
        Larger sizes in the upper part of the range are more forgiving when stems are thicker than planned.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="scenarioCard">
      <h3>Best for Beginners</h3>
      <p>
        A small mixed assortment is safer than relying on one exact size, because home seedling batches are rarely perfectly uniform.
      </p>
