</section>

<section class="guideSection">
  <h2>How This Fits Into a Beginner Grafting Setup</h2>

  <p>
    Clip size is only one part of the process, but it is one of the parts that can quietly sabotage everything else. Even with good cuts and good healing conditions, poor clip fit makes the union harder to hold.
  </p>

  <p>
    For home gardeners, the simplest approach is to buy a small useful range and match the clip to the seedling on the day of grafting, not to an idealized plan made a week earlier.
  </p>

